The paper discusses the design and implementation of a reservoir computing circuit using cellular automata and memristive output. This falls under the subfield of neural networks and machine learning, which is covered by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of resistive random-access memory (ReRAM) also suggests a potential fit for cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), as ReRAM is a relatively new technology. The design and fabrication of the circuit may also fall under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), while the use of memristive output could be relevant to cs.EM (Electromagnetics) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
